                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From reading the Brenlo area thread, it becomes clear to me that a number of people are acting under the rather deluded assumption that, at some point in the past (some think it's as recently as early PoP) you could "refresh" charm by casting it on your pet.
<br />

<br />
This is nonsense.
<br />

<br />
Charm is a detrimental spell.   Casting a detrimental spell on your pet does NOTHING.
<br />

<br />
Now, admittedly, I can see how people might be fooled by this because until very recently, charm had no "your target has been charmed" message, so it gave exactly the same feedback (i.e. none) when cast on your pet as when cast on any other mob.
<br />

<br />
HOWEVER.  Charm has never been "refreshable".  The max duration on our lower level charms is longer, but that is it. Period.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
