                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Spelling, word misuse attacks are lame. Many, including scientists, improperly use words all the time. Hell, there are journalist and authors who depend on writing words to make a living that make simple mistakes similar to the one between "effect" and "affect." 
<br />

<br />
You used to be able to cast charm on a charmed pet. This did not give you an error message. However, recasting charm on a charmed pet did absolutely nothing but waste your mana as the duration of charm was never refreshed. I've been playing since jul'99 and have tried this before. As have many others who have been playing a long time. They were merely recasting charm on a pet. Not refreshing charm as charm never refreshed. There is a huge difference between the two.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
