                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You could, in fact, do this on a PvP server in the past.  Back when you could attack your own pet, you could simply recharm by re casting charm.  Now its the same as blue servers.  Casting on your pet does nothing. 
<br />

<br />
For the longest time it would cause you to lose your pet and it would become an npc.  Then, for a while, your pet would 'poof' if you cast on it.  In either time frame, one could 'recharm' by just casting charm.  
<br />

<br />
To some mages  <img src="images/smiles/icon_confused.gif" alt="icon_confused.gif" border="0" />  it was quite fun to park a air pet at lets say in G Fay at the CB zoneline, cast on it, lose it and it became an NPC.  It would invis itself, and own low level characters as they zoned out from the trains of CB.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
